definitions.definition: Fully sufficient; found in copious supply; in great quantity; overflowing.
examples: Blackberries are abundant in this part of the country in October, so we always make lots of jam.
an abundant selection of carpets to choose from

definitions.definition: Richly supplied ; wealthy ; possessing in great quantity.
Being an abundant number , i.e. less than the sum of all of its divisors except itself.
definitions.dating_raw: First attested in the mid 16 century.

main_definition: Fully sufficient; found in copious supply; in great quantity; overflowing. [First attested around 1350 to 1470.]
secondary_definitions: Richly supplied ; wealthy ; possessing in great quantity. [First attested around 1350 to 1470.]
( mathematics ) Being an abundant number , i.e. less than the sum of all of its divisors except itself. [First attested in the mid 16 century.]
